69. Build a PHP function to change the following array's all values to upper or lower case.

Sample arrays :
$Color = array('A' => 'Blue', 'B' => 'Green', 'c' => 'Red');
Expected Output :
Values are in lower case.
Array ( [A] => blue [B] => green [c] => red )
Values are in upper case.
Array ( [A] => BLUE [B] => GREEN [c] => RED )

<?php
// Sample array
$Color = array('A' => 'Blue', 'B' => 'Green', 'c' => 'Red');

// Function to change all values to lowercase
function toLowerCase($arr) {
    return array_map('strtolower', $arr);
}

// Function to change all values to uppercase
function toUpperCase($arr) {
    return array_map('strtoupper', $arr);
}

// Convert to lowercase
$lower = toLowerCase($Color);
echo "Values are in lower case.<br>";
print_r($lower);

echo "<br><br>";

// Convert to uppercase
$upper = toUpperCase($Color);
echo "Values are in upper case.<br>";
print_r($upper);
?>
Output:
Values are in lower case.
Array ( [A] => blue [B] => green [c] => red )

Values are in upper case.
Array ( [A] => BLUE [B] => GREEN [c] => RED )
